class SortingLinkedList<T : Comparable<T>> {

    private val list = LinkedList<T>()

    fun add(element: T) {
        list.add(element)
    }

    fun reverseRecursive() {
        list.reverseRecursive()
    }

    override fun toString(): String {
        return list.toString()
    }
}

import kotlin.math.PI
import kotlin.math.TWO_PI
import kotlin.math.HALF_PI
import kotlin.math.dist
import kotlin.math.lerp
import kotlin.math.map
import kotlin.math.toDegrees
import kotlin.math.ease
import kotlin.math.ease as ease


val PI = kotlin.math.PI
val TWO_PI = kotlin.math.TWO_PI
val HALF_PI = kotlin.math.HALF_PI

fun dist(x1: Float, y1: Float, x2: Float, y2: Float): Float =
    kotlin.math.dist(x1, y1, x2, y2)

fun lerp(x1: Float, x2: Float, t: Float): Float =
    kotlin.math.lerp(x1, x2, t)

fun map(x1: Float, x2: Float, y1: Float, y2: Float, t: Float): Float =
    kotlin.math.map(x1, x2, y1, y2, t)

fun toDegrees(radians: Float): Float =
    kotlin.math.toDegrees(radians)

fun ease(t: Float): Float =
    kotlin.math.ease(t)

fun ease(t: Float, easeFactor: Float): Float =
    kotlin.math.ease(t, easeFactor)
